	<main>
		<img width="2048" height="984" src="https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-plankton-photo-essay.jpg" class="singlepostthumb wp-post-image" alt="noble necklace worm laden with eggs" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" srcset="https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-plankton-photo-essay.jpg 2048w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-plankton-photo-essay-520x250.jpg 520w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-plankton-photo-essay-1200x577.jpg 1200w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-plankton-photo-essay-768x369.jpg 768w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-plankton-photo-essay-1536x738.jpg 1536w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-plankton-photo-essay-900x432.jpg 900w" sizes="(max-width: 2048px) 100vw, 2048px" /><div class="post-thumbnail-caption">This noble necklace worm, laden with eggs, will eventually release her developed larvae into the water column as plankton. Photo by the Hakai Institute</div>
			<article class="main container col4">
								<header class="maincol">
										<h1 class="pagetitle">Peeking into the Ocean’s Microscopic Baby Boom</h1>
										<h2 class="dek singlepagecontainer">Springtime delivers the world’s tiniest zoo babies.</h2>
										<section class="singlebyline singlepagecontainer">
						<h3 class="invis">Authored by</h3>
						Text by  
										<a href="https://hakaimagazine.com/profiles/kelly-fretwell/" class="tagmanager" id="author_link_top" >Kelly Fretwell</a> and  
										<a href="https://hakaimagazine.com/profiles/adrienne-mason/" class="tagmanager" id="author_link_top" >Adrienne Mason</a>								<br/>
							Photos by the Hakai Institute 								<br/>
												</section>
					 
					<aside class="singlebydatewords singlepagecontainer">
